org.janusgraph.core.schema

Interface JanusGraphSchemaElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Namifiable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EdgeLabel, Index, InternalRelationType, InternalVertexLabel, JanusGraphIndex, JanusGraphSchemaType, PropertyKey, RelationType, RelationTypeIndex, SystemRelationType, VertexLabel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseKey, BaseLabel, BaseRelationType, BaseVertexLabel, EdgeLabelVertex, EmptyRelationType, ImplicitKey, JanusGraphIndexWrapper, PropertyKeyVertex, RelationTypeIndexWrapper, RelationTypeVertex, VertexLabelVertex

    public interface JanusGraphSchemaElement
extends Namifiable
    Marks any element that is part of a JanusGraph Schema. JanusGraph Schema elements can be uniquely identified by their name.

    A JanusGraph Schema element is either a JanusGraphSchemaType or an index definition, i.e. JanusGraphIndex or RelationTypeIndex.

    Author:
    Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)
